    "text_3": {
      "type": "content-block",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_1": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "What's Out: Loud Logos and Try-Hard Prints",
            "tag": "h2",
            "size": "h3",
            "font": "serif"
          }
        },
        "text_1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>We'll say it: the era of neon polos and chaotic patterns is finally fading. There's a difference between standing out and screaming for attention, golf fashion is leaning into the former. If your gear still looks like a party store exploded on it, it might be time to refresh the rotation.</p><p>Equally on the way out? Sloppy silhouettes. The too-big polo, the saggy shorts, the forgotten belt, it's giving <em>1997 muni dad</em>, and not in a cool, vintage way. Today's golfer is more considered. Still casual, still comfortable, but undeniably more tailored and intentional. The goal is to look like you belong on the course <em>and</em> at an outdoor lunch spot after your round. Not like you rolled out of bed and happened to bring clubs.</p><p>TRENDYGOLF has plenty of streamlined upgrades to swap in, think crisp polos from <strong>J.Lindeberg</strong>, tapered trousers from <strong>Greyson</strong>, and structured outerwear from <strong>RLX Ralph Lauren</strong>. Your swing deserves better. So does your closet.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_1",
        "text_1"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "alignment": "left",
        "enable_animation": true
